20Sunday%20(Mar%2016)%20after%20lifting%20off%20from%20Kennedy%20Space%20Centre%20in%20Florida%20on%20Friday%20(Mar%2014)%2C%20aboard%20the%20Falcon%209%20rocket.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20likely%20that%20Ms%20Williams%20and%20Mr%20Wilmore%20would%20have%20developed%20a%20condition%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bbaby%20feet%26quot%3B%20wherein%20the%20soles%20of%20an%20astronaut's%20feet%20become%20soft%20like%20a%20baby's%20after%20spending%20months%20in%20space%20--%20making%20it%20painful%20for%20them%20to%20walk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20walking%20on%20Earth%2C%20our%20feet%20face%20a%20lot%20of%20resistance%20in%20the%20form%20of%20gravity%20and%20friction%2C%20which%20makes%20the%20skin%20on%20the%20soles%20thicker.%20It%20protects%20us%20from%20feeling%20discomfort%20and%20pain%20while%20protecting%20us%20from%20general%20wear%20and%20tear.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20after%20spending%20months%20in%20space%2C%20the%20harder%20skin%20comes%20off%20and%20the%20feet%20are%20left%20very%20soft%20and%20tender.%C2%A0Until%20the%20feet%20build%20up%20hard%20skin%20again%2C%20which%20can%20take%20from%20a%20few%20weeks%20to%20a%20couple%20of%20months%2C%20walking%20can%20be%20uncomfortable%20and%20even%20distressing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EBone%20density%20loss%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20baby%20feet%2C%20the%20lack%20of%20gravity%20causes%20significant%20and%20often%20irreparable%2C%20bone%20density%20loss.%20As%20per%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noindex%2Cnofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fmissions%2Fstation%2Fiss-research%2Fcounteracting-bone-and-muscle-loss-in-microgravity%2F%5C%22%3ENASA%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20every%20month%20in%20space%2C%20astronauts'%20weight-bearing%20bones%20become%20roughly%20one%20per%20cent%20less%20dense%20if%20they%20don't%20take%20precautions%20to%20counter%20this%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuscles%2C%20usually%20activated%20by%20simply%20moving%20around%20on%20Earth%2C%20also%20weaken%20because%20they%20no%20longer%20need%20to%20work%20as%20hard.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noindex%2Cnofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fchilling-prediction-made-by-new-nostradamus-with-india-link-comes-true-7926328%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20Chilling%20Prediction%20Made%20By%20'New%20Nostradamus'%20With%20India%20Link%20Comes%20True%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EBlood%20volume%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20blood%20volume%20also%20shrinks%20in%20an%20astronaut's%20body%20as%20the%20heart%20does%20not%20have%20to%20pump%20blood%20against%20gravity%20and%20has%20to%20work%20much%20less%20hard.%20The%20way%20the%20blood%20flows%20in%20the%20body%20also%20changes.%20It%20slows%20in%20some%20areas%20which%20can%20lead%20to%20clots.%20Fluids%20also%20don't%20come%20down%2C%20or%20drain%2C%20as%20easily.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fluid%20build-up%20also%20changes%20the%20shape%20of%20the%20eyeballs%20and%20weakens%20the%20vision.%20It%20is%20perhaps%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20why%20most%20astronauts%20are%20seen%20wearing%20spectacles%20in%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ERadiation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20dangerous%20impacts%20of%20spending%20time%20in%20space%20is%20radiation%20exposure.%20While%20Earth's%20atmosphere%20and%20magnetic%20field%20shield%20humans%20from%20high%20levels%20of%20radiation%2C%20such%20protection%20is%20not%20available%20for%20astronauts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENASA%20states%20that%20astronauts%20are%20majorly%20exposed%20to%20three%20types%20of%20radiation.%20These%20include%20particles%20trapped%20in%20Earth's%20magnetic%20field%2C%20solar%20magnetic%20particles%20from%20the%20Sun%20and%20the%20galactic%20cosmic%20rays.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742091420000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2Flpi4flcg_butch-wilmore-and-sunita-williams_625x300_10_March_25.jpg%22%2C%22or